  "prompt": "What is the most underrated problem in the life of a musician?",
  "response": "One of the most underrated problems in the life of a musician is mental health issues, particularly the stress of constant comparison and the pressure to succeed in a highly competitive industry. Musicians often face scrutiny from peers, fans, and the media, leading to feelings of inadequacy, anxiety, and depression. The pressure to maintain a public persona, paired with the ups and downs of the music business\u2014such as gig cancellations, financial instability, and varying levels of recognition\u2014can significantly impact mental well-being.\n\nAdditionally, the isolation that can come from touring or being in a creative bubble often exacerbates these mental health issues. Many musicians may feel they cannot express their struggles or seek help due to the stigma surrounding mental health in the arts, making it a particularly challenging and underrated aspect of their lives.",
